The '''Académie Internationale de Droit Constitutionnel''' or '''International Academy for Constitutional Law''' ('''IACL''') was created in 1984 and is based in [[Tunis]], [[Tunisia]].

The official language of the academy is [[French language|French]]. Its current members come from more than 50 different countries. The aim of the academy is to promote the study of [[constitutional law]] with an international approach, and by comparing different systems.



