[[File:Barthelmarktzelt2005gross.jpg|thumb|Beer tent]] The '''Barthelmarkt''' is an annual [[Volksfest]] ([[beer festival]] and [[travelling funfair]]) in [[Manching]], near [[Ingolstadt]], [[Germany]]. It is held on the last weekend of August and lasts four days. Every year, about 250.000 people visit it.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.onetz.de/deutschland-und-die-welt-r/lokales/geselligkeitsclub-hogerer-knuepfen-kontakte-bei-audi-und-am-barthelmarkt-mit-eslarner-showband-im-hotel-d30189.html|title=Geselligkeitsclub "Hogerer" knüpfen Kontakte - Bei Audi und am Barthelmarkt: Mit "Eslarner Showband" im Hotel|last=Tag|first=Medienhaus Der Neue|website=onetz.de|access-date=2016-06-06}}</ref>
Though first mentioned in 1354, its roots can be traced back as early as to the 1st century BC, when the [[Roman Empire|Romans]] established a cattle market in the area.
The name "Barthelmarkt" stems from [[St. Bartholomew]], the patron saint of the local church.<ref>Donaukurier.de Newsjournal, 08.26.2015: [http://www.donaukurier.de/themen/barthelmarkt/art351906,3113920 ''Warum der Barthelmarkt "Barthelmarkt" heißt]</ref>
