{{Infobox rockunit | name = Calizas de Lychnus Formation | image = | caption = | type = [[Geological formation]] | age = [[Mesozoic]] | period = Mesozoic | prilithology = | otherlithology = | namedfor = | namedby = | region = [[Castille and Leon]] | country = [[Spain]] | coordinates = | unitof = | subunits = | underlies = | overlies = | thickness = | extent = | area = | map = | map_caption = }}
The '''Calizas de Lychnus Formation''' is a [[Mesozoic]] geologic [[Formation (geology)|formation]] in northern central [[Spain]]. [[Dinosaur]] remains diagnostic to the [[genus]] level are among the fossils that have been recovered from the formation.<ref name="dinosaurdistribution">Weishampel, et al. (2004). "Dinosaur distribution." Pp. 517-607.</ref>
