{{italic title}}
'''''Morocco Times''''' was an [[English language]] [[Morocco|Moroccan]] [[Internet]]-based [[newspaper]], the first of its kind.

==History==
''Morocco Times'' was started on 22 November 2004, and was owned by the [[Maroc Soir Group]], a publishing house that owns several of Morocco's major newspapers.<ref>{{cite news|title=Moroccan Press Needs an Effective Newspaper in English|url=http://moroccotimes.over-blog.com/pages/Moroccan_Press_Needs_an_Effective_Newspaper_in_English-1733322.html|accessdate=12 October 2013|work=Morocco Times}}</ref> It stopped being published at the end of October 2006, a few weeks before its second birthday.<ref>{{cite news|title=Electronic Journalism: New Anglophone Newspaper Launched in Morocco|url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/Electronic+Journalism%3A+New+Anglophone+Newspaper+Launched+in+Morocco.-a0311369201|accessdate=12 October 2013|work=PR.com|date=8 December 2012}}</ref>
The Morocco Times is not to be confused with The Moroccan Times, a news Magazine launched in 2014.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://moroccantimes.com/|title=The Moroccan Times - Your Gateway to Morocco News|publisher=}}</ref>

