{{Infobox road |country=KHM |type=Hwy |route=4 }} [[File:Road 4 to Sihanouk.JPG|thumb|right|200px|National Highway 4 in Chbar Mon in [[Phnom Penh]].]] '''National Highway 4''' or National Road No.4 (10004) (in [[Khmer language|Khmer]] ផ្លូវជាតិលេខ ៤) is one of the national [[highway]]s of [[Cambodia]]. With a length of {{convert|230|km|abbr=on}},<ref>Discovering Sihanoukville Municipality, p. 665, in "Cambodia in the Early 21st Century", Phnom Penh, 2004, {{ISBN|2-9513524-0-9}}</ref> it connects the capital of [[Phnom Penh]] with [[Sihanoukville (city)|Sihanoukville]] in the south-west.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20060825003757/http://www.cambodiaportal.com/index.php?mymenu=destinations&submenu=nationalroadnetwork&ext=Y&submenutitle=National%20Road%20Network Cambodian national road network]</ref> Sihanoukville is the only international sea port of Cambodia. Consequently, NH4 is one of the most important highways of the country for economical purposes. The road was built in the 1950s coinciding with the construction of the port.<ref>Discovering Sihanoukville Municipality, p. 665, in "Cambodia in the Early 21st Century", Phnom Penh, 2004, {{ISBN|2-9513524-0-9}}</ref>
The road was built especially for the transport of merchandise between the capital and the port by heavy trucks and containers. Portions of NH4 was considered a [[toll road]] with three stations to collect fees. All toll stations have now been removed, the road is now toll free.<ref>http://www.phnompenhpost.com/national/national-road-4-toll-fees-nixed </ref> It is also considered the most dangerous road of Cambodia due to several traffic accidents and little control by authorities.<ref>Real Travel: [http://realtravel.com/sihanoukville-cambodia-travel-guide-d658440-1.2344218.html Travel Guide for Sihanoukville], Link retrieved on 5th Feb 2009</ref>
== Description ==
The road begins at the junction of [[Pochentong Avenue]] and [[National Highway 3 (Cambodia)|National Highway 3]]. The junction, located in western [[Phnom Penh]] near the [[Phnom Penh International Airport]], is in the [[Sangkat]] Chaom Chau &ndash; [[Dangkor District]]. The road initially heads westerly then curves toward the south west.
After the first toll station, NH4 enters [[Kandal Province]]. It then crosses [[Kampong Speu Province|Kampong Speu]], [[Koh Kong Province|Koh Kong]] and [[Sihanoukville Province|Sihanoukville]] provinces. In the territory of Koh Kong, at Chamkar Luong, National Road 48 branches off west toward Koh Kong town and the [[Thailand|Thai]] border. The junction with NH3, which leads to [[Kampot (city)|Kampot]] to the east beyond to the [[Vietnam]]ese border is in the territory of Sihanoukville, at [[Prey Nob]] District.
